<DocLayout title="Policy & Research" description="AEGIS published papers, NIST submissions, policy responses, and research.">
  <h1>Policy &amp; Research</h1>

  <p>
    The AEGIS Initiative engages with policymakers, standards bodies, and the
    research community to advance governance-first approaches to AI safety. This
    section collects published papers, formal submissions, and policy responses.
  </p>

  <hr />

  <section>
    <h2>NIST Submissions</h2>
    <p>
      AEGIS has submitted formal public comments and position papers to the
      National Institute of Standards and Technology (NIST) as part of ongoing
      AI safety and governance rulemaking processes.
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <strong>"AEGIS: A Constitutional Governance Architecture — NIST AI RMF Position Statement"</strong><br />
        Submitted March 2026. Formal position paper on constitutional governance as an AI Risk Management Framework implementation pattern. DOI pending.
      </li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <hr />

  <section>
    <h2>Published Papers</h2>
    <p>
      Preprints are available on Zenodo. Peer-reviewed versions will be linked
      when published.
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <strong>"AEGIS: A Constitutional Governance Architecture for Autonomous AI Agents"</strong><br />
        Submitted to <em>IEEE Computer</em>, Special Issue on AI Governance and Compliance.<br />
        DOI: <a href="https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.19223924">10.5281/zenodo.19223924</a> — 81 views, 14 downloads.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>"ATX-1: AEGIS Threat Matrix for AI Governance Systems"</strong><br />
        Submitted to <em>IEEE Data Descriptions</em>.<br />
        DOI: <a href="https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.19251098">10.5281/zenodo.19251098</a> — machine-readable STIX 2.1 threat intelligence dataset.
      </li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <hr />

  <section>
    <h2>NCCoE Engagement</h2>
    <p>
      AEGIS has responded to the National Cybersecurity Center of Excellence
      (NCCoE) project on AI Agent Identity and Access Management.
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <strong>"AEGIS: AI Agent Identity, Authorization, and Governance"</strong><br />
        Response to NCCoE AI Agent Identity &amp; Access Management project. Submitted March 2026.
      </li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <hr />

  <section>
    <h2>Policy Responses</h2>
    <p>
      AEGIS responds to emerging policy proposals and regulatory frameworks that
      affect AI governance, safety, and security.
    </p>
    <p class="placeholder">
      Responses to White House AI frameworks, congressional proposals, and
      international regulatory developments are in development and will be
      published here as they are finalized.
    </p>
  </section>

  <hr />

